  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager/ Coordinator",
  "description": "<h3>Job Scope / Responsibilities</h3><p><strong>1. Project Planning & Control</strong></p><ul><li><p>Define project scope, objectives, deliverables, timelines, and budgets</p></li><li><p>Develop and maintain detailed project plans and schedules</p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress and ensure timely delivery within approved scope and cost</p></li></ul><p><strong>2. Project Execution & Coordination</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead and coordinate cross-functional teams, vendors, and contractors</p></li><li><p>Assign tasks and manage resources effectively</p></li><li><p>Ensure deliverables meet quality and compliance standards</p></li></ul><p><strong>3. Stakeholder & Communication Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Act as the main liaison between management, clients, and stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Prepare and present project status reports and documentation</p></li><li><p>Facilitate meetings, reviews, and project updates</p></li></ul><p><strong>4. Risk, Issue & Change Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Identify, assess, and mitigate project risks and issues</p></li><li><p>Manage project changes using formal change-control procedures</p></li><li><p>Resolve conflicts and escalate issues where necessary</p></li></ul><p><strong>5. Budget & Cost Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Track project expenditures and control costs</p></li><li><p>Manage procurement and vendor payments where applicable</p></li><li><p>Ensure efficient use of project resources</p></li></ul><p><strong>6. Documentation & Governance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain accurate project documentation and records</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with company policies, contractual terms, and regulatory requirements</p></li><li><p>Conduct post-project reviews and implement improvements</p></li></ul><p><strong>7. Leadership & Continuous Improvement</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide leadership, guidance, and motivation to project team members</p></li><li><p>Mentor junior staff when required</p></li><li><p>Recommend improvements to project management processes</p></li></ul><h2>Job Requirements / Qualifications</h2><h3>Education & Certification</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma / Degree in <strong>Project Management, Business, Engineering, IT, or related field</strong></p></li><li><p>Project management certification (e.g. <strong>PMP, PRINCE2, Agile</strong>) is an advantage</p></li></ul><h3>Experience</h3><ul><li><p>Proven track record of managing multiple projects successfully</p></li><li><p>Experience working with cross-functional teams and external stakeholders</p></li></ul>",
